Types of STL Algorithms:

Sorting Algorithms:

std::sort: Sorts a container or range of elements in ascending order.

std::stable_sort: Sorts a container but preserves the relative order of elements that are considered equal.

std::partial_sort: Partially sorts a container, leaving the remaining elements in an unspecified order.

Searching Algorithms:

std::find: Searches for an element in a range and returns an iterator to it if found.
std::find 会遍历从 container.begin() 到 container.end() 这个范围内的所有元素，直到找到匹配的 value 为止。
如果找到了匹配的元素，std::find 会返回一个指向该元素的迭代器。
如果没有找到，std::find 会返回 container.end()


std::binary_search: Checks whether an element exists in a sorted range.

std::lower_bound: Finds the first position where an element can be inserted without breaking the order (in a sorted container).

Manipulation Algorithms:

std::reverse: Reverses the order of elements in a range.

std::rotate: Rotates the elements of a range.

std::shuffle: Randomly shuffles the elements of a container.

std::unique: Removes consecutive duplicate elements.

Numeric Algorithms:

std::accumulate: Computes the sum of a range of elements.

std::inner_product: Computes the sum of the products of corresponding elements in two ranges.

std::partial_sum: Computes partial sums (cumulative sums) for a range of elements.

Comparison Algorithms:

std::equal: Compares two ranges for equality.

std::lexicographical_compare: Compares two ranges element by element lexicographically.

Set Operations:

std::set_union: Computes the union of two sets.

std::set_intersection: Computes the intersection of two sets.

std::set_difference: Computes the difference of two sets.

For_each and Transformations:

std::for_each: Applies a function to every element in a range.

std::transform: Applies a transformation to each element of a range.

Partitioning Algorithms:

std::partition: Reorganizes elements in a range so that all elements satisfying a condition come before those that do not.

std::stable_partition: Similar to partition, but maintains the relative order of the elements.


