1. Understanding std::stack:

std::stack is an adapter container in C++ that works on top of other containers, typically std::deque or std::vector.

It provides a LIFO (Last In, First Out) structure with operations like:

push(): Add an element to the stack.

pop(): Remove the top element from the stack.

top(): Get the element at the top of the stack.

size(): Get the number of elements in the stack.

empty(): Check if the stack is empty.




